> Lemon is our go-to ingredient for brightening up any meal, and this dish is positively
> bursting with citrusy goodness! Seared chicken is drizzled with a creamy, lemon-spiked
> pan sauce that would taste good on pretty much anything. On the side, there's roasted
> zucchini topped with a crispy Parmesan topping—plus scallion-studded Israeli couscous
> tossed with both lemon juice and zest. When life gives you lemons, you know what to do.

== Parmesan Asparagus & Roasted Zucchini ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and slice @zucchini{1}(trimmed and sliced crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick rounds).
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, separating whites from
greens). Zest and halve @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}
with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary or trim and discard woody bottom ends
from asparagus. (Save zucchini for another use.)

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the
@Tuscan heat spice{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Arrange zucchini in a single layer so they are touching but not overlapping. Top
with panko mixture.

Roast on top rack until zucchini is tender and panko is golden brown and crispy,
~{15-18%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli or asparagus for zucchini; roast 15-20 minutes for broccoli or
> 10-12 minutes for asparagus.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with remaining
@Tuscan heat spice{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Scallion Couscous ==

While chicken cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%oz}; stir until toasted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @water{3/4%cup}, half the @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is
tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Creamy Lemon Butter Sauce ==

Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add remaining
@chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, and a squeeze of lemon juice to
taste. Simmer until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and combined. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

To pot with couscous, add juice from half the lemon, half the lemon zest, half the
scallion greens, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; stir to combine.

> TIP: If couscous seems dry, add a splash of water. For extra richness, stir in
> 1 TBSP butter.

Divide couscous, chicken, and zucchini between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken.
Top with remaining scallion greens and lemon zest. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.